WEBVTT

00:58.184 --> 00:59.477
SHAGGY:
That's my pal.

01:00.144 --> 01:01.604
Scooby-Dooby-Doo!

01:18.955 --> 01:20.039
Hurry up, Pedro.

01:20.206 --> 01:23.501
It's almost time for the ghost
of General Juan Carlos to appear.

01:23.668 --> 01:26.504
I-- 1 think we better go home, Diego.

01:26.671 --> 01:28.339
Don't be scared, amigo.

01:28.506 --> 01:31.425
If the ghost appears,
| will protect you. |-

01:31.592 --> 01:33.261
[MANIACAL LAUGHING NEARBY]

01:35.972 --> 01:38.057
[YELLS]

01:39.183 --> 01:40.309
It's the ghost. Run!

01:40.476 --> 01:41.936
[GHOST LAUGHING]

01:51.654 --> 01:55.700
This vacation will be terrific.
I've always wanted to see Puerto Rico.

01:55.866 --> 01:57.326
Well, here it is, Daphne.

01:57.493 --> 01:58.911
[CANON FIRES]

01:59.662 --> 02:00.997
Hey, was that thunder?

02:01.163 --> 02:04.500
Like, maybe it was a 21-gun salute
for our arrival here.

02:04.959 --> 02:06.335
Twenty-one guns?

02:06.502 --> 02:08.420
All at once, huh?

02:08.586 --> 02:09.880
[CHUCKLES]

02:10.047 --> 02:11.257
[GIGGLES]

02:11.424 --> 02:12.508
All at once.

02:12.675 --> 02:14.135
[LAUGHING]

02:15.469 --> 02:19.015
-Scoob, it wasn't that funny.
-It wasn't?

02:19.181 --> 02:20.850
Oh.

02:21.017 --> 02:22.893
Hmm. Maybe it was a sonic boom.

02:23.060 --> 02:26.522
Fred, look.
What's going on over there?

02:26.856 --> 02:29.025
FRED:
They must be searching for something.

02:29.191 --> 02:30.568
Let's go take a look.

02:30.735 --> 02:31.902
Good idea, Velma.

02:32.069 --> 02:35.072
Shag, you and Scooby keep an eye
on The Mystery Machine.

02:35.239 --> 02:39.535
Okay, Fred. We'll be right here
chowing down on the native fruit.

02:41.579 --> 02:45.583
Ooh, pineapple.
Oh, boy, oh, boy, oh, boy.

02:45.750 --> 02:48.753
Sorry, Scoob.
| think | got the last one.

02:53.632 --> 02:57.219
No, Scoob.
Pineapple's no good for you.

03:00.181 --> 03:01.223
[YELPS]

03:03.184 --> 03:05.269
Besides, it's bad for your complexion.

03:05.770 --> 03:09.732
And you probably
wouldn't like it anyway.

03:14.070 --> 03:15.738
[GRUNTS]

03:21.118 --> 03:24.997
Like, it's kind of sour. Mm-mm.

03:25.164 --> 03:28.292
Scooby-Doo.

03:30.878 --> 03:32.296
Like, I've been robbed.

03:32.463 --> 03:34.632
It was the crime of the century, sefior.

03:34.799 --> 03:35.883
What happened?

03:36.050 --> 03:38.803
OFFICER: Our museum was robbed
of many artifacts.

03:38.969 --> 03:42.306
These treasures must not be allowed
to leave Puerto Rico.

03:42.473 --> 03:44.850
We'd be happy
to help you search for them.

03:45.017 --> 03:48.813
Ah, gracias, senorita,
but our police force can handle it.

03:48.979 --> 03:51.107
VELMA:
Okay, officer. Good luck.

03:51.273 --> 03:53.984
Come on, girls.
We've got a lot of sights to see.

03:54.777 --> 03:59.073
SHAGGY:
Scooby, get back here. Scooby-Doo.

04:01.992 --> 04:06.038
Like, | know you're here someplace.
Come on out with that hot pineapple.

04:06.205 --> 04:08.290
[GIGGLES]

04:11.377 --> 04:12.795
[YELPS]

04:15.464 --> 04:17.507
Now that's more like it.

04:17.675 --> 04:20.136
SCOOBY: Shaggy.
-What is it, Scoob?

04:20.302 --> 04:22.680
Over here. Look. Look.

04:25.516 --> 04:27.852
Like, that's really interesting, Scooby.

04:28.018 --> 04:31.188
But I'm sure there are better things
to see in Puerto Rico.

04:31.355 --> 04:32.815
Huh?

04:33.774 --> 04:36.652
| hope the police
catch those thieves soon.

04:36.819 --> 04:39.738
Right, before the treasures
are smuggled out of the country.

04:39.905 --> 04:41.782
[CANON FIRES]

04:42.533 --> 04:45.035
-What was that?
-More thunder and lightning?

04:45.202 --> 04:48.372
| don't think so, Daphne.
It came from that castle up there.

04:48.831 --> 04:52.042
It sounded like some kind of explosion.
We'd better check it out.

04:52.209 --> 04:54.628
Like, can we take a vote on that?

04:54.795 --> 04:56.464
| vote we check it out.

04:56.630 --> 04:58.549
VELMA: Me too.
-Count me in.

04:58.716 --> 05:00.050
All those against?

05:00.217 --> 05:03.512
-Me.
VELMA: That's three to two.

05:04.472 --> 05:06.932
Three, four, five?

05:07.099 --> 05:09.101
We win.

05:09.560 --> 05:11.479
We lose.

05:12.730 --> 05:16.901
Listen, you two can stay out here
if you want to, but we're going inside.

05:17.067 --> 05:19.236
Like, what do you
think we are? Cowards?

05:23.365 --> 05:25.075
You're right. We are.

05:25.242 --> 05:27.328
[CHUCKLES]

05:27.536 --> 05:29.705
[SCOOBY GIGGLES]

05:30.164 --> 05:33.209
DAPHNE:
Boy, this fortress looks awfully old.

05:33.375 --> 05:34.418
VELMA:
Itis.

05:34.585 --> 05:37.755
El Morro Fortress dates back
over 400 years.

05:37.922 --> 05:42.092
Like, on a clear day, | bet you could see
all of Puerto Rico from here.

05:42.259 --> 05:43.302
Yeah.

05:43.469 --> 05:44.637
Oow!

05:44.803 --> 05:48.098
Hot. Hot, hot. Ooh! Hot, hot, hot!

05:48.432 --> 05:54.021
Hot? Come on, Scoob. Like, this cannon
probably hasn't been fired in centuries.

05:54.980 --> 05:57.441
Zoinks! It is hot.

05:57.608 --> 06:01.111
Like, | wonder if those booms we heard
were from this cannon.

06:01.278 --> 06:02.905
SCOOBY:
| don't know.

06:03.072 --> 06:04.114
Yikes!

06:04.281 --> 06:05.616
Scooby, look behind you.

06:07.952 --> 06:11.288
Out of my fortress!

06:11.455 --> 06:12.873
SCOOBY:
Ghost.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.959
Be gone!

06:15.334 --> 06:16.377
Good idea.

06:16.544 --> 06:20.965
Like, let's let begones be begones
and split.

06:21.632 --> 06:23.092
[GULPS]

06:28.097 --> 06:31.308
Couldn't we just, uh, you know,
like, talk it over?

06:31.475 --> 06:35.980
The time for talking is past, sefior.

06:36.522 --> 06:38.607
[BOTH YELL]

06:40.317 --> 06:42.403
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

06:44.071 --> 06:45.531
[SHAGGY GRUNTS]

06:45.698 --> 06:47.408
SHAGGY:
Follow me, Scoob.

06:47.575 --> 06:49.827
SCOOBY:
I'm with you.

06:49.994 --> 06:52.079
[LAUGHING]

06:55.916 --> 06:58.586
Hi, guys. Like, any luck?

06:58.752 --> 07:00.671
No. Nothing, Shaggy.

07:00.963 --> 07:02.506
Did you see anything unusual?

07:02.798 --> 07:04.466
Yeah, there was this-- Hey.

07:04.633 --> 07:06.719
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

07:08.220 --> 07:10.931
Nope, not a thing. Right, Scoob?

07:11.098 --> 07:12.600
Uh-huh.

07:13.350 --> 07:15.185
Why don't | believe that?

07:15.352 --> 07:16.854
[BOTH CHUCKLE NERVOUSLY]

07:17.021 --> 07:20.274
Come on. Let's get some rest
for our big fishing trip tomorrow.

07:24.445 --> 07:27.865
SHAGGY: Careful, Scoob.
If they find out there's a ghost up there...

07:28.032 --> 07:30.868
-...you know they'll wanna check it out.
-Gotcha.

07:31.201 --> 07:35.706
Fortress? Sure. | know all about it,
and its ghost.

07:35.873 --> 07:36.999
Ghost?

07:37.166 --> 07:39.209
Would you tell us about it,
Captain Eddie?

07:39.376 --> 07:43.839
Well, Velma, legend has it
that the spirit of Juan Carlos...

07:44.006 --> 07:48.510
...a 16th century Spanish general,
is still guarding the old fortress.

07:48.677 --> 07:53.223
And whenever he has a mind to,
he likes to shoot off the old cannons.

07:53.390 --> 07:55.726
That must be
what we heard last night.

07:55.893 --> 07:58.228
Heh-heh-heh. You heard it, eh?

07:58.562 --> 08:02.566
Yeah. Like, what they don't know
won't hurt us.

08:14.536 --> 08:15.621
SCOOBY:
Help!

08:16.330 --> 08:18.957
-Oh, no.
-Scooby. Shaggy.

08:21.585 --> 08:23.671
[SHAGGY CHOKING]

08:29.093 --> 08:30.511
Uh-oh.

08:38.184 --> 08:39.645
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY YELLING]

08:48.237 --> 08:49.363
[SHARK CRASHES]

09:04.044 --> 09:05.379
[YELLS]

09:20.728 --> 09:22.187
[CHUCKLES]

09:25.899 --> 09:27.359
BOTH:
Whoa!

09:27.901 --> 09:31.613
SHAGGY:
Whoa! Whoa!

09:34.074 --> 09:35.909
Nice try, you guys.

09:36.076 --> 09:40.122
Like, he's probably telling his friends
right now about the ones that got away.

09:40.289 --> 09:42.624
Yeah, thank goodness.

09:42.791 --> 09:44.793
Zoinks! He's still on the line.

09:45.085 --> 09:47.755
Oh, no, you don't, you sea monster.
Ha-ha-ha.

09:47.921 --> 09:50.549
Old Shag doesn't give up that easy.

09:50.716 --> 09:51.800
Gotchal!

09:53.302 --> 09:54.344
Yipes!

09:54.511 --> 09:58.307
SHAGGY: Stop! Get us off!
It's vicious. It's mean. It's--

09:58.474 --> 10:01.143
-A parachute.
-Parachute?

10:01.310 --> 10:03.812
What would a parachute
be doing in the ocean?

10:03.979 --> 10:05.147
The backstroke?

10:05.314 --> 10:06.774
[GIGGLES]

10:07.983 --> 10:11.153
No. There's no water damage
to the fabric at all.

10:11.320 --> 10:14.239
And look, it's much too small
for a man to use.

10:14.406 --> 10:16.283
[FOGHORN BLARES]

10:17.159 --> 10:21.330
EDDIE: Uh, ahem. Fog's rolling in.
We better get to shore.

10:21.789 --> 10:26.335
Great. Like, | wanna get out of these
cold clothes and into a hot meal.

10:26.502 --> 10:28.670
Brr! Yeah, me too.

10:28.837 --> 10:31.673
We'll all grab a bite
before we go back to the fortress.

10:31.840 --> 10:34.843
-Right. The fortress? With the ghost?
-The fortress?

10:35.010 --> 10:37.846
So you did see something last night.

10:38.013 --> 10:39.056
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

10:39.223 --> 10:42.267
Like, oops.
Uh, didn't we mention the ghost?

10:42.434 --> 10:44.186
Ha-ha-ha. Silly us.

10:44.353 --> 10:45.854
Yeah. Hee-hee-hee.

10:46.647 --> 10:47.940
Like, I'm sorry, guys...

10:48.106 --> 10:51.985
...but this time, we'll just stay here
and guard the entrance.

10:52.152 --> 10:54.154
Well, suit yourself, Shaggy.

10:59.326 --> 11:01.954
Like, maybe we better go with them,
huh, Scoob?

11:02.120 --> 11:03.205
No way.

11:03.372 --> 11:05.249
Scooby.

11:06.834 --> 11:09.169
Hey!

11:10.003 --> 11:11.088
Scooby?

11:11.255 --> 11:13.882
Scooby-Doo, where are you?

11:14.049 --> 11:16.426
Over here.

11:19.054 --> 11:23.934
The ghost-- | mean, the coast is clear.
Come on, Scoob.

11:28.605 --> 11:30.691
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

11:32.860 --> 11:34.945
BOTH:
Whoa!

11:36.947 --> 11:39.032
[GHOST LAUGHING]

11:48.333 --> 11:50.210
SHAGGY & SCOOBY:
Whoa!

11:52.671 --> 11:56.008
-Like, I think we're goners, Scoob.
-Oh, no.

11:56.174 --> 11:58.260
[GHOST LAUGHING]

12:07.853 --> 12:11.315
| will teach you to defy me.

12:11.481 --> 12:15.444
-Like, it's doomsville for sure, Scoob.
-Help.

12:19.406 --> 12:21.491
[GHOST LAUGHING]

12:22.743 --> 12:24.453
SHAGGY & SCOOBY:
Help!

12:25.162 --> 12:28.790
Fred, Daphne,
it's the ghost of Juan Carlos!

12:29.207 --> 12:31.251
Let's get him.

12:36.006 --> 12:38.508
SCOOBY:
Fred! Velma!

12:38.675 --> 12:42.721
SCOOBY:
That's it. Oh, Daphne. Down here.

12:45.057 --> 12:47.851
FRED: Scoob, Shaggy,
what are you doing down there?

12:48.018 --> 12:50.479
Screaming for help.

12:50.646 --> 12:51.897
Help!

12:52.564 --> 12:55.400
Here, grab hold.

12:59.655 --> 13:00.906
[GULPS]

13:01.073 --> 13:04.826
Phew! That's a long way down.

13:06.244 --> 13:08.747
Hey, like, wait.
You can't leave us here.

13:09.039 --> 13:12.417
The answers to this mystery
just might be at the Hall of Records.

13:12.584 --> 13:16.755
Right. And somebody has to keep an eye
on things here while we check it out.

13:16.922 --> 13:20.425
-Why us?
-Yeah, like, why us?

13:20.592 --> 13:23.011
Don't worry, guys.
The ghost won't show up again.

13:23.178 --> 13:25.514
Lightning never strikes twice
in the same place.

13:26.139 --> 13:30.394
Oh, yeah.
Like, he's got a point, Scoob.

13:31.228 --> 13:32.729
Yikes!

13:35.190 --> 13:37.234
Fred, come back!

13:37.401 --> 13:40.737
Daphne! Velma!

13:41.613 --> 13:44.157
MAN: Why do you disturb me
so late at night?

13:44.324 --> 13:47.869
VELMA: There's something strange
going on at El Morro Fortress, sefior.

13:48.036 --> 13:51.707
And we think there might be a connection
with the recent museum robbery.

13:51.873 --> 13:54.418
Hey, Velma, Fred, look at this.

13:56.545 --> 14:00.382
VELMA: This old map shows a tunnel
leading to the fortress.

14:00.549 --> 14:03.218
FRED: And it begins here
where the museum is.

14:05.053 --> 14:06.513
I'm sorry, it is late.

14:06.680 --> 14:08.557
-You must all leave.
DAPHNE: But--

14:08.890 --> 14:10.809
You must leave!

14:12.519 --> 14:14.229
FRED:
Boy, what got into him?

14:17.899 --> 14:19.735
DAPHNE:
Well, where to now?

14:19.901 --> 14:22.863
VELMA: To the next piece of the puzzle:
the museum.

14:23.030 --> 14:24.740
FRED:
Right, Velma.

14:31.121 --> 14:33.623
Like, do you see anything, Scoob?

14:33.790 --> 14:35.000
No.

14:35.167 --> 14:37.669
-You see anything?
-Nope.

14:37.836 --> 14:39.671
FRED:
Okay, there's the museum.

14:39.838 --> 14:42.299
And according to the map
at the Hall of Records...

14:42.466 --> 14:44.468
...the tunnel is right underneath us.

14:44.634 --> 14:47.596
So there must be an entrance
inside the museum.

14:47.763 --> 14:51.600
FRED: But why didn't the police find it?
VELMA: It must be very well hidden.

14:51.767 --> 14:54.019
Let's see if we can get inside
to check it out.

15:00.609 --> 15:02.152
Oops!

15:03.028 --> 15:04.446
You found it, Daphne.

15:04.613 --> 15:06.865
There's an opening
under this phone booth.

15:10.577 --> 15:13.205
VELMA:
Jinkies, this phone booth is a fake.

15:13.371 --> 15:15.499
DAPHNE:
No wonder the police missed it.

15:15.665 --> 15:16.708
FRED:
Follow me.

15:24.216 --> 15:27.135
We've been walking
for almost an hour.

15:27.302 --> 15:30.222
Yeah. It seems to go on forever.

15:32.224 --> 15:34.893
Look, there's something
at the end of the tunnel.

15:44.486 --> 15:47.739
DAPHNE: Wow.
VELMA: Amazing. Look at all this stuff.

15:47.906 --> 15:49.908
FRED:
The stolen treasures.

15:50.075 --> 15:53.829
VELMA: We better head back right away
and get the police.

15:56.373 --> 15:58.458
[RUMBLING]

15:58.875 --> 16:01.211
FRED:
Look out, girls!

16:05.715 --> 16:07.926
-What's that?
-l don't know, Scoob.

16:08.093 --> 16:10.428
It's coming from that direction.

16:15.851 --> 16:19.312
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

16:19.521 --> 16:21.606
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

16:28.113 --> 16:30.198
BOTH:
Whoa! Whoa!

16:37.998 --> 16:39.791
Like, what are you guys doing here?

16:39.958 --> 16:42.043
[GHOST LAUGHING]

16:43.670 --> 16:44.921
SCOOBY:
Yipe!

16:45.088 --> 16:48.383
Never mind answering.
It's good to see you.

16:50.051 --> 16:52.053
Hey. Like, you know
we're trapped in here.

16:52.220 --> 16:53.972
Trapped, | tell you. Ha-ha-ha!

16:54.181 --> 16:58.226
We'll never get out of here. Never.
It's over. It's over, | tell you.

16:58.393 --> 17:00.145
We're finished! Ha-ha-ha!

17:00.520 --> 17:02.898
Finished! I'm finished.

17:03.064 --> 17:06.902
Now that you're finished, come here
and help us look for a way out of here.

17:07.068 --> 17:08.862
Hey, guys. Look at these.

17:09.029 --> 17:11.740
More parachutes
like the one we found before.

17:11.906 --> 17:15.952
Parachutes? Great.
Like, maybe we can skydive out of here.

17:16.118 --> 17:18.747
Scoob, this is no time
to be fooling around.

17:18.914 --> 17:21.458
Put down those cannonballs.

17:21.625 --> 17:23.667
All right.

17:25.753 --> 17:28.757
FRED:
Hey, what's this? A hollow cannonball.

17:28.924 --> 17:31.927
Like, this mystery gets crazier
and crazier.

17:32.093 --> 17:34.471
Hollow cannonballs. Parachutes.

17:34.638 --> 17:38.099
Hmm. Maybe it's not so crazy after all.

17:38.266 --> 17:41.269
VELMA: Look what | found, guys.
-Good work, Velma.

17:43.021 --> 17:44.439
DAPHNE:
We're free.

17:44.606 --> 17:46.608
Great. Let's get out of here. Fast.

17:46.775 --> 17:49.945
-Wait just a minute.
-Just a minute? Just a minute?

17:50.111 --> 17:53.615
Like, that ghost is out there someplace
and he wants to do us in, Fred.

17:53.782 --> 17:55.951
That's just why we've got
to trap him, Shaggy.

17:56.117 --> 17:57.452
And I've got a plan.

17:57.619 --> 18:00.497
We take one
of those parachutes and...

18:03.667 --> 18:04.793
FRED:
It's all set.

18:04.960 --> 18:08.296
Now, we'll split up and try to make
as much commotion as possible...

18:08.463 --> 18:12.133
...to draw the ghost here. Then we'll try
to lead him through this doorway.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.302
It's him. Run!

18:14.469 --> 18:16.263
Yikes!

18:19.432 --> 18:22.894
-Hey, you two, come back.
-What scared them?

18:23.687 --> 18:25.355
MAN:
Perhaps it was |.

18:26.273 --> 18:28.358
-Fred.
-Who are you?

18:28.525 --> 18:30.527
Permit me to introduce myself.

18:30.694 --> 18:34.197
| am Inspector Armandres
of Puerto Rico Police.

18:34.364 --> 18:35.490
ALL [IN UNISON]:
Police?

18:35.657 --> 18:36.700
INSPECTOR:
Correct.

18:36.866 --> 18:38.868
I've been on this case
from the beginning.

18:39.160 --> 18:42.789
Allow me to congratulate you
on locating part of the missing treasure.

18:42.956 --> 18:44.040
Just part of it?

18:44.207 --> 18:48.003
INSPECTOR: Unfortunately,
our ghost friend has already managed...

18:48.169 --> 18:50.297
...to move much of it
out of the country.

18:50.463 --> 18:52.549
[GHOST LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

18:53.925 --> 18:55.218
ALL:
There he is!

19:04.394 --> 19:06.980
INSPECTOR:
Quick. After him.

19:09.983 --> 19:12.360
| think we've lost him, Scoob.

19:16.614 --> 19:18.742
SCOOBY:
The ghost.

19:21.661 --> 19:23.830
FRED:
He went this way.

19:27.208 --> 19:28.877
There he is. Up there.

19:31.046 --> 19:33.548
GHOST:
You cannot stop me!

19:33.715 --> 19:35.550
He's heading back
toward the dungeons.

19:46.728 --> 19:50.190
DAPHNE: Oh, no. A dead end.
FRED: It's a trap.

19:50.357 --> 19:52.067
[GHOST LAUGHING]

19:57.989 --> 20:01.826
GHOST:
You are trapped forever, my amigos.

20:01.993 --> 20:04.079
[GHOST LAUGHING]

20:09.959 --> 20:12.796
Help! Help!

20:16.716 --> 20:18.176
[GHOST YELLING]

20:20.720 --> 20:21.971
Scooby?

20:22.138 --> 20:25.892
Quick, Shag,
pull that lever and let us out.

20:30.480 --> 20:34.734
GHOST:
Aah! Get this thing off of me.

20:35.985 --> 20:39.155
INSPECTOR:
You are finished, General Juan Carlos.

20:39.322 --> 20:40.990
Or whoever you are.

20:42.826 --> 20:45.412
ALL:
Captain Eddie.

20:46.371 --> 20:49.999
We located the rest of the treasures
on his boat, inspector.

20:50.166 --> 20:52.085
Meddling young fools.

20:52.252 --> 20:54.838
Could've gotten away
with a king's ransom.

20:55.004 --> 20:59.509
Like, | still don't understand how he got
all those things past the police.

20:59.676 --> 21:02.846
Through the tunnel that leads here
from the museum, Shaggy.

21:03.012 --> 21:06.474
And then he didn't get it past
the police, Shag. He got it over them.

21:06.641 --> 21:08.351
With the cannon.

21:08.518 --> 21:10.353
Over them?

21:10.520 --> 21:14.858
Captain Eddie put the stuff inside these
canisters with the parachutes attached.

21:15.024 --> 21:18.319
Then he aimed the old cannon
toward his boat anchored out at sea...

21:18.486 --> 21:21.030
...and shot the treasure
into his fishing nets.

21:21.197 --> 21:24.492
He used the old legend of the ghost
to scare people away...

21:24.659 --> 21:26.870
...until he had all the stuff on his boat.

21:27.036 --> 21:30.206
Yeah. A couple of more nights
and | would've had it all.

21:30.373 --> 21:32.292
Take him away.

21:37.046 --> 21:40.008
VELMA:
Well, I'm glad that mystery's over.

21:40.175 --> 21:42.218
You said it, Velma.

21:42.385 --> 21:45.388
Like, now we can get down
to some serious vacationing.

21:45.555 --> 21:48.558
Hey, that's some fortress
you're building, Shaggy.

21:48.725 --> 21:51.853
Yeah, and this one
doesn't have a ghost.

21:52.020 --> 21:53.688
[GROANING NEARBY]

21:55.482 --> 21:58.401
SHAGGY:
Zoinks! Like, it's a sand ghost.

21:58.568 --> 22:01.237
[GIGGLES]

22:01.404 --> 22:05.450
Scooby-Dooby-Doo.
